#. i18n: ectx: property (toolTip), widget (QCheckBox, chkAcceptAuthenticatedPackets)
#: openvpnadvanced.ui:539
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Allow remote peer to change its IP address and/or port number such as due "
"to\n"
"DHCP (this is the default if --remote is not used). --float when specified "
"with --remote\n"
"allows an OpenVPN session to initially connect to a peer at a known "
"address,\n"
"however if packets arrive from a new address and pass all authentication "
"tests, the\n"
"new address will take control of the session. This is useful when you are "
"connecting\n"
"to a peer which holds a dynamic address such as a dial-in user or DHCP "
"client.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Essentially, --float tells OpenVPN to accept authenticated packets from any "
"address,\n"
"not only the address which was specified in the --remote option."
msgstr ""
"Il permitte a par remote de modificar su adresse  IP e/o numero de portotal "
"como debite  a\n"
"DHCP (isto es le predefinite si --remote non es usate). --float quando "
"specificate con --remote\n"
"permitte a un session de OpenVPN de connecter initialmente a un par a un "
"adresse cognoscite,\n"
"totevia si pacchettos arriva ex un nove adresse e passa omne tests de "
"authentication, le\n"
"nove adresse prendera controlo del session. Isto es utile quando tu es "
"connectente\n"
" a un par que mantene un adresse dynamic tal como un usator dial-in o un "
"cliente DHCP.\n"
" \n"
"\n"
"Essentialmente, --float dice a OpenVPN de acceptar pacchettos authenticate "
"ab ulle addresse,\n"
"non solmente le addresse que esseva specificate in le option  --remote."

